<chapter xml:id="sections">
<title>Sections</title>
<simpara>Documents structured into sections are easier to read. Asciidoctor supports
sections, subsections, subsubsections, and so on. The number of <literal>=</literal> indicates
the depth.</simpara>
<section xml:id="references">
<title>References</title>
<simpara>Sometimes its useful to be able to reference other sections, such as
<xref linkend="references"/>, or <xref linkend="sections"/>, or <link linkend="references">let&#8217;s make the references great again!</link> Even
paragprahs <link linkend="paragraph">can be referenced</link>.</simpara>
<simpara xml:id="paragraph">All you need to do so is put the name of the reference at its
start.</simpara>
</section>
</chapter>
